<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Advisory vote to approve executive compensation as required by law; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Seven shareholder proposals contained in this proxy statement; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Other matters if properly raised. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Only shareholders of record on April&nbsp;3, 2019, or their proxy holders may vote at the meeting. Attendance at the meeting is limited to shareholders or their proxy
holders and ExxonMobil guests. Only shareholders or their valid proxy holders may address the meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">This booklet includes the formal notice of the meeting and
proxy statement. The proxy statement tells you about the agenda, procedures, and rules of conduct for the meeting. It also describes how the Board operates, gives information about our director candidates, and provides information about the other
items of business to be conducted at the meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Financial information is provided separately in the booklet, 2018 Financial Statements and Supplemental
Information, enclosed with the proxy materials or made available online to all shareholders. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Your vote is important.<B> </B>Even if you own only a few shares, we
want your shares to be represented at the meeting. You can vote your shares by Internet, toll-free telephone call, or proxy card. A<B> </B>Summary of 2019 Proxy Voting Results<B> </B>will be available at <I>exxonmobil.com</I> after the annual
shareholders meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">To attend the meeting in person, please follow the instructions on page 6. An audio webcast and a report on the meeting will be available on
our website at <I>exxonmobil.com.</I> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center">Sincerely, </P> <P STYLE="font-size:30pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:13pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B><A NAME="toc686227_1"></A>PROXY SUMMARY AND VOTING MAP </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Shareholders are asked to consider the materials included in this proxy statement and to vote on the following: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:13pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%"></TD></TR>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:13pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B>Director Attendance </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">During 2018, the ExxonMobil Board met nine times. Directors, on average, attended approximately 99&nbsp;percent of Board and committee meetings during 2018. No director
attended less than 75&nbsp;percent of such meetings. ExxonMobil&#146;s <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors held seven executive sessions in 2018. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="42%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="18%"></TD>
<TD></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:48pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B>9</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B>99%</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b">Board meetings</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b">during 2018</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-bottom:0pt; margin-top:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b">Director average</FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-bottom:1pt; margin-top:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b">attendance</FONT></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:13pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B>Board Highlights </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The ExxonMobil Board is comprised of directors with a diverse mix of backgrounds, knowledge, and skills. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b">&#147;ExxonMobil recognizes the strength and effectiveness of the Board reflects the balance, experience, and diversity of the individual
directors; their commitment; and importantly, the ability of directors to work effectively as a group in carrying out their responsibilities. ExxonMobil seeks candidates with diverse backgrounds who possess knowledge and skills in areas of
importance to the Corporation.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b">&#150; ExxonMobil Director Selection Guidelines </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:13pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B>Board Tenure </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board actively refreshes its
membership, reflected in an average tenure for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors that is lower than the applicable <I>Standard</I><I></I><I>&nbsp;&amp; Poor&#146;s</I> 500 average of 8.1 years. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="51%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="45%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b">Average tenure of <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-</FONT></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b">employee directors</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>
</TABLE> </DIV><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; margin-left:3%; width:49%;padding-right:0%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Risk Management </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g686227g67k23.jpg" ALT="LOGO">

</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">

 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:1pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">10 of 10 Directors </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Scientific/Technical/Research
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g686227g12t44.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:1pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">7 of 10 Directors </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Current/Former CEO/Field
Prominence </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:13pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B><A NAME="toc686227_2"></A>GENERAL INFORMATION </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:20pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Who May Vote </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Shareholders of ExxonMobil, as recorded in our stock register
on April&nbsp;3, 2019, may vote at the meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>How to Vote </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">You may
vote in person at the meeting or by proxy. We recommend you vote by proxy even if you plan to attend the meeting. You can always change your vote at the meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Important Notice Regarding the Availability of Proxy Materials for the Shareholders Meeting to be held on May&nbsp;29, 2019: </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><B>The 2019 Proxy Statement, 2018 Summary Annual Report, and 2018 Financial Statements are available at </B><B><I>www.edocumentview.com/xom. </I></B><B></B></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Notice and Access </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">We distribute proxy
materials to many shareholders via the Internet under the Securities and Exchange Commission&#146;s (&#147;SEC&#146;s&#148;) &#147;Notice and Access&#148; rules, thereby capturing cost and environmental benefits. On or about April&nbsp;11, 2019, we
mailed a Notice Regarding the Availability of Proxy Materials (&#147;Notice&#148;) that contains information about our 2019 annual shareholders meeting and instructions on how to view all proxy materials on the Internet. Also included are
instructions on how to vote and how to request a paper or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-mail</FONT> copy of the proxy materials. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Electronic Delivery of
Proxy Statement and Annual Report Documents </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">For shareholders receiving proxy materials by mail, you can elect to receive an
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-mail</FONT> in the future that will provide electronic links to these documents. Opting to receive your proxy materials online will save the Company the cost of producing and mailing documents to your home or
business, and will also give you an electronic link to the proxy voting site. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt"><B>Shareholders of Record: </B>If you vote on the Internet at <I>www.investorvote.com/exxonmobil, </I>simply follow the
prompts for enrolling in the electronic proxy delivery service. You may enroll in the electronic proxy delivery service at any time in the future by going directly to <I>www.computershare.com/exxonmobil</I>. You may also revoke an electronic
delivery election at this site at any time. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt"><B>Beneficial Shareholders:</B> If you hold your shares in a brokerage account, you may also have the opportunity to
receive copies of the proxy materials electronically. Please check the information provided in the proxy materials mailed to you by your bank or broker regarding the availability of this service. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>How Proxies Work </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">ExxonMobil&#146;s Board of Directors is asking for your
proxy. Giving us your proxy means you authorize us to vote your shares at the meeting in the manner you direct. </P>

to vote, we will vote your shares as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">If you hold shares through someone else, such as a stockbroker, you will receive materials from that firm asking how you want to vote. Check the voting form used by
that firm to see if it offers Internet or telephone voting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Voting Shares in the ExxonMobil Savings Plan </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Trustee of the ExxonMobil Savings Plan will vote Plan shares as participants direct. To the extent participants do not give instructions, the Trustee will vote
shares as it thinks best. The proxy card serves to give voting instructions to the Trustee. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Revoking a Proxy </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">You may revoke your proxy before it is voted at the meeting by: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Confidential Voting </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Independent inspectors count the votes. Your individual
vote is kept confidential from us unless special circumstances exist. For example, a copy of your proxy card will be sent to us if you write comments on the card. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Quorum </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">In order to carry on the business of the meeting, we must have a
quorum. This means at least a majority of the outstanding shares eligible to vote must be represented at the meeting, either by proxy or in person. Treasury shares, which are shares owned by ExxonMobil itself, are not voted and do not count for this
purpose. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Votes Required </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt"><B>Election of Directors Proposal:</B> Under ExxonMobil&#146;s bylaws, a director nominee must receive a majority of votes
cast in order to be elected to the Board of Directors in a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-contested</FONT> election. In a contested election (in which the number of nominees exceeds the number of directors to be elected), the plurality vote
standard under New Jersey law would apply. Under plurality voting, the director nominee with the most votes for a particular seat is elected for that seat. Abstentions and broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> are not counted for
purposes of the election of directors. A broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-vote</FONT> occurs when a bank, broker, or other holder of record that is holding shares for a beneficial owner does not vote on a particular proposal because the
record holder does not have discretionary voting power and has not received instructions from the beneficial owner. <B>If you own shares through a broker, you must give the broker instructions to vote your shares in the election of directors.
Otherwise, your shares will not be voted.</B> </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Our Corporate Governance Guidelines, which can be found in the Corporate Governance
section of our website at <I>exxonmobil.com/governance, </I>state that all directors will stand for election at the annual meeting of shareholders. In any <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-contested</FONT> election of directors, any director
nominee who receives a greater number of votes AGAINST his or her election than votes FOR such election shall tender his or her resignation. Within 90 days after certification of the election results, the Board of Directors will decide, through a
process managed by the Board Affairs Committee and excluding the nominee in question, whether to accept the resignation. Absent a compelling reason for the director to remain on the Board, the Board shall accept the resignation. The Board will
promptly disclose its decision and, if applicable, the reasons for rejecting the tendered resignation on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">8-K</FONT> filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt"><B>Other Proposals:</B> Approval of the ratification of the appointment of independent auditors, the advisory vote to
approve executive compensation, and the shareholder proposals require the favorable vote of a majority of votes cast. Only votes FOR or AGAINST these proposals count. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Abstentions count for quorum purposes, but not for voting. Broker <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-votes</FONT> count as votes FOR the ratification
of the appointment of independent auditors but do not count for voting on any of the other proposals. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Annual Meeting Admission </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Only shareholders or their proxy holders and ExxonMobil guests may attend the meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>For safety and security reasons, cameras, smartphones, recording equipment, electronic devices, computers, large bags, briefcases, packages, and firearms or other
weapons will not be permitted in the building</B>.<B> </B>In addition, each shareholder and ExxonMobil guest will be asked to present valid government-issued picture identification, such as a driver&#146;s license, before being admitted to the
meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">For registered shareholders, an admission ticket is the upper part of your proxy card or the full Notice. Please bring the admission ticket with you to
the meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">If your shares are held in the name of your broker, bank, or other nominee, you must bring to the meeting an account statement or letter from the
nominee indicating that you beneficially owned the shares on April&nbsp;3, 2019, the record date for voting. You may receive an admission ticket in advance by sending a written request with proof of ownership to the address listed below under
Contact Information. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Shareholders who do not present admission tickets at the meeting will be admitted only upon verification of ownership at the admission
counter. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>


<IMG SRC="g686227g94y05.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
&nbsp;&nbsp;Audio Webcast of the Annual Meeting </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">You are invited to visit our website at <I>exxonmobil.com </I>to hear the audio
webcast at 9:30 a.m. Central Time, on Wednesday, May&nbsp;29, 2019. An archived copy of this webcast will be available for one year. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Conduct of the Meeting </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Chairman has broad responsibility and legal authority to conduct the annual meeting in an orderly and timely manner. This authority includes establishing rules for
shareholders who wish to address the meeting. Only shareholders or their valid proxy holders may address the meeting. Copies of these rules will be available at the meeting. The Chairman may also exercise broad discretion in recognizing shareholders
who wish to speak and in determining the extent of discussion on each item of business. In light of the number of business items on this year&#146;s agenda and the need to conclude the meeting within a reasonable period of time, we cannot ensure
that every shareholder who wishes to speak on an item of business will be able to do so. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Dialogue can usually be better accomplished with interested parties
outside the meeting and, for this purpose, we have provided a method on our website at <I>exxonmobil.com/directors</I> for raising issues and contacting the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors either in writing or
electronically. The Chairman may also rely on applicable law regarding disruptions or disorderly conduct to ensure that the meeting is conducted in a manner that is fair to all shareholders. Shareholders making comments during the meeting must do so
in English so that the majority of shareholders present can understand what is being said. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="99%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:13pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B><A NAME="toc686227_3"></A>BOARD OF DIRECTORS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:20pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B><A NAME="toc686227_4"></A>Corporate Governance </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Overview </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board of Directors and its committees perform a number of
functions for ExxonMobil and its shareholders, including: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Overseeing the management of the Company on your behalf, including oversight of risk management; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Reviewing ExxonMobil&#146;s long-term strategic plans; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Exercising direct decision-making authority in key areas, such as declaring dividends; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Selecting the Chief Executive Officer (&#147;CEO&#148;) and evaluating the CEO&#146;s performance; and
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Reviewing development and succession plans for ExxonMobil&#146;s top executives. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board has adopted Corporate Governance Guidelines that govern the structure and functioning of the Board and set out the Board&#146;s position on a number of
governance issues. A copy of our current Corporate Governance Guidelines is posted on our website at <I>exxonmobil.com/guidelines</I>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">At least annually, the Board
and each of the Board committees conduct an evaluation of its performance and effectiveness. Any potential changes to the committees&#146; charters are also considered at least once a year. <B> </B></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Risk Oversight </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Risk<B>
</B>oversight is the responsibility of the full Board of Directors. The Board throughout the year participates in reviews with management on the Company&#146;s business, including identified risk factors. As a whole, the Board reviews litigation and
other legal matters; political contributions, budget, and policy; lobbying costs; developments in climate science and policy; the <I>Energy Outlook</I>, which projects world energy supply and demand to 2040; stewardship of business performance; and
long-term strategic plans. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board and/or the Public Issues and Contributions Committee visit an ExxonMobil operations site each year. These visits allow the
directors to better understand local issues and to discuss issues such as safety, environmental performance, technology, products, industry and corporate standards, and community involvement associated with the Company&#146;s business. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">In addition, existing committees help the Board carry out its responsibility for risk oversight by focusing on specific key areas of risk: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="63%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="35%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-2.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201; The Audit Committee oversees
risks associated with financial and accounting matters, including compliance with legal and regulatory requirements, and the Company&#146;s financial reporting and internal control systems. The Committee also periodically reviews cybersecurity risks
and preparedness and ExxonMobil&#146;s overall risk management approach and structure.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-2.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8194;&#8201;The Board Affairs Committee oversees risks
associated with corporate governance, including Board structure and succession planning.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-2.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8194;&#8201;The Compensation Committee helps ensure that the
Company&#146;s compensation policies and practices encourage long-term focus, support the retention and development of executive talent, and discourage excessive risk taking.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-2.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8194;&#8201;The Public Issues and Contributions Committee
oversees operational risks such as those relating to employee and community safety, health, environmental performance, including actions taken to address climate-related risks, and security matters.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g686227g30a04.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="3"> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-2.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8194;&#8201;The Finance Committee oversees risks associated with financial instruments, financial policies and strategies, and capital structure.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board receives regular updates from the committees, and
believes this structure is best for overseeing risk. <B> </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Board Leadership Structure </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board believes that the decision as to who should serve as Chairman and/or CEO is the proper responsibility of the Board. The Board retains authority to amend the
bylaws to separate the positions of Chairman and CEO at any time and will carefully consider the pros and cons of such separation or combination. <B>At the present time, the Board believes the interests of all shareholders are best served through a
leadership model with a combined Chairman/CEO position and an independent Presiding Director.</B> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The current CEO possesses an
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-depth</FONT> knowledge of the Company; its integrated, multinational operations; the evolving energy industry supply and demand fundamentals; and the array of challenges to be faced. This knowledge was gained
through more than 26 years of successful experience in progressively more senior positions, including domestic and international responsibilities. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board
believes that these experiences and other insights put the CEO in the best position to provide broad leadership for the Board as it considers strategy and as it exercises its fiduciary responsibilities to shareholders. Further, the Board has
demonstrated its commitment and ability to provide independent oversight of management. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">8&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>

<IMG SRC="g686227g34r14.jpg" ALT="LOGO">

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board is comprised entirely of independent directors except for the CEO, and 100&nbsp;percent of the Audit,
Compensation, Board Affairs, and Public Issues and Contributions Committee members are independent. Each independent director has access to the CEO and other Company executives on request, may call meetings of the independent directors, and may
request agenda topics to be added or dealt with in more detail at meetings of the full Board or an appropriate Board committee. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">In addition, after considering
evolving governance practices and shareholder input regarding Board independence, the Board established the role of Presiding Director. <B>The Board believes the Presiding Director provides effective independent Board leadership.</B> Steven S
Reinemund serves as Presiding Director and is expected to remain in the position at least through the annual meeting of shareholders. In accordance with the specific duties prescribed in the Corporate Governance Guidelines, the Presiding Director
chairs and approves the agenda for executive sessions of the independent directors, which are held several times per year, normally coincident with meetings of the Board and without the CEO or other management present; chairs meetings of the Board
in the absence of the Chairman; and works closely with the Chairman in developing Board agendas, topics, schedules, and in reviewing materials provided to the directors. <B> </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Director Qualifications </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board has adopted guidelines outlining the
qualifications sought when considering <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director candidates. These Guidelines for the Selection of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Employee</FONT> Directors (&#147;Selection Guidelines&#148;),
which are published on our website at <I>exxonmobil.com/directorguidelines</I>, are reviewed annually and state in part: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">&#147;ExxonMobil recognizes the strength
and effectiveness of the Board reflects the balance, experience, and diversity of the individual directors; their commitment; and importantly, the ability of directors to work effectively as a group in carrying out their responsibilities. ExxonMobil
seeks candidates with diverse backgrounds who possess knowledge and skills in areas of importance to the Corporation.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The qualifications we consider for
director candidates include: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Individuals who have achieved prominence in their fields; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Diversity of experiences and backgrounds, including gender and race/ethnic diversity; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Experience and demonstrated expertise in managing large, relatively complex organizations, such as that of CEOs or
next-level executives of a significant company or organization with global responsibilities; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Financial and other risk management expertise; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Experience with cyclical businesses, such as commodities. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Other considerations include: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">A substantial majority of the Board must meet independence standards as described in the Corporate Governance Guidelines;
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">All candidates must be free from any relationship with management or the Corporation that would interfere with the exercise
of independent judgment; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Candidates should be committed to representing the interests of all shareholders and not any particular constituency; and
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board is comprised of directors with an effective mix of backgrounds, knowledge, and skills that the Board
considers helpful in fulfilling its oversight role. The chart below provides a summary of the collective competencies of the Board nominees and explains why these are important: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">Experience serving as a CEO or other prominent leader provides unique perspectives to help the Board independently oversee ExxonMobil&#146;s CEO and
management. Having this experience also increases the Board&#146;s understanding and appreciation of the many facets of modern international organizations, including strategic planning, financial reporting and compliance, and risk oversight.</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">managing large,</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">relatively complex</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial"><B>Large / Complex Organizations</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">ExxonMobil is among the largest corporate groups in the world. Experience leading a large organization provides practical insights on the challenges
and opportunities that such complex businesses face.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial"><B>Global Business Leadership</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">ExxonMobil conducts business around the world. Having a global business perspective aids the Board in understanding diverse business environments,
economic conditions, and cultures associated with our global workforce and activities.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">Our Company operates in many different places and under varied conditions. Having experience with operational matters and requirements assists the
Board in understanding the issues that may face ExxonMobil in its worldwide activities, including maintenance needs, labor relations, and regulatory requirements.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">risk management</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">expertise</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial"><B>Financial Experience</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">ExxonMobil&#146;s business involves complex financial management, capital allocation, and reporting issues. An understanding of finance and financial
reporting is valuable in order to promote effective capital allocation, robust controls, and oversight.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>

</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial"><B>Risk Management</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">The
scale, scope, and complexity of ExxonMobil&#146;s business raises a multitude of interdependent risks, which can vary over time. Experience in effectively identifying, prioritizing, and managing a broad spectrum of risks can help the Board
appreciate, anticipate, and assist the Company in managing the risks that face its varied businesses.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>

</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:12pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">Experience on one</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">or more boards of</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">significant public</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-profit</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">organizations</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial"><B>Public Company Board </B><BR>An understanding of public
company reporting responsibilities and the issues commonly faced by public companies is important to navigating governance issues faced by ExxonMobil.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:10pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.08em">


<IMG SRC="g686227g45k07.jpg" ALT="LOGO">

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">academic, scientific,</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">or research activities</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial"><B>Scientific / Technical / Research Experience</B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.11em; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">ExxonMobil is a leader in research and technology, from finding and producing oil and gas, to developing new products, mitigating emissions, and
protecting the environment. It is helpful for Board members to have these competencies, as science and technology are cornerstones to our businesses.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Director Independence</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Our Corporate Governance Guidelines require that a substantial majority of the Board consists of independent directors. In general, the Guidelines require that an
independent director must have no material relationship with ExxonMobil, directly or indirectly, except as a director. The Board determines independence on the basis of the standards specified by the New York Stock Exchange (&#147;NYSE&#148;), the
additional standards referenced in our Corporate Governance Guidelines, and other facts and circumstances the Board considers relevant.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g686227g61r18.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Under ExxonMobil&#146;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, a director will not be independent if a reportable &#147;related person
transaction&#148; exists with respect to that director or a member of the director&#146;s family for the current or most recently completed fiscal year. See the Guidelines for Review of Related Person Transactions posted on the Corporate Governance
section of our website and described in more detail under Related Person Transactions and Procedures on pages 13 and 14. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board has reviewed relevant
relationships between ExxonMobil and each <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director and director nominee to determine compliance with the NYSE standards and ExxonMobil&#146;s additional standards. The Board has also evaluated
whether there are any other facts or circumstances that might impair a director&#146;s independence. <B>Based on that review, the Board has determined that all ExxonMobil <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors and nominees
are independent.</B> The Board has also determined that each member of the Audit, Board Affairs, Compensation, and Public Issues and Contributions Committees (see membership table on page 15) is independent<B> </B>based on both applicable NYSE
standards and the Company&#146;s independence standards for each of these committees. The Company&#146;s standards for each committee are included in their respective charters and are posted on our website at<I> exxonmobil.com/guidelines</I>.
Website materials are not part of this proxy statement or the accompanying solicitation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">In recommending that each director and nominee be found independent, the
Board Affairs Committee reviewed the following transactions, relationships, or arrangements. All matters described below fall within the NYSE and ExxonMobil independence standards. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Board Succession </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">As noted
in the committee information that follows, the Board Affairs Committee is responsible for identifying director candidates. The Committee seeks new candidates in several ways: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Recommendations made by the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors. These recommendations are
developed based on the directors&#146; own knowledge and experience in a variety of fields and on the research conducted by ExxonMobil staff at the Committee&#146;s direction. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Engagement of an executive search firm. The firm brings forward potential director candidates for the Committee to consider
and helps research candidates identified by the Committee. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Recommendations made by employee directors, shareholders, and others. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">All recommendations, regardless of the source, are evaluated on the same basis against the criteria contained in the Selection Guidelines. The Committee has also
instructed its executive search firm to include diversity as part of the candidate search criteria. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Shareholders may send recommendations for director candidates
to the Secretary at the address given under Contact Information on page 7. A submission recommending a candidate should include: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Sufficient biographical information to allow the Committee to evaluate the candidate in light of the Selection Guidelines;
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Information concerning any relationship between the candidate and the shareholder recommending the candidate; and
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Material indicating the willingness of the candidate to serve if nominated and elected. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The procedures by which shareholders may recommend nominees have not changed materially since last year&#146;s proxy statement. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Company seeks to have a diverse Board representing a range of backgrounds, knowledge, and skills relevant to the Company&#146;s business and the needs of the Board,
and as part of the search process, considers highly qualified candidates, including women and minorities. The Committee does not use quotas but considers diversity along with the other requirements of the Selection Guidelines when evaluating
potential new directors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Board Tenure </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board does not impose tenure
limits on its directors, other than a mandatory retirement age of 72 and the requirement to stand for election annually. Given the complexity and breadth of our business and its long investment horizons, the Board considers longevity of service and
experience of great value. The Board also believes that its director compensation approach, which limits the vesting of restricted shares until retirement, closely aligns directors with the interests of long-term shareholders. The Board seeks to
achieve a balance of diversity and experience in the composition of the Board. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">All ExxonMobil directors stand for election at the annual meeting. <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> directors cannot stand for election after they have reached age 72, unless the Board makes an exception on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">case-by-case</FONT></FONT>
basis. Employee directors resign from the Board when they are no longer employed by ExxonMobil. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">As of April&nbsp;1, 2019, the average tenure of <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors standing for election is 6.5 years, well below the average of S&amp;P 500 companies of 8.1 years (per <I>2018 Spencer Stuart Board Index</I>). </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B>Non-Employee Director Tenure </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="52%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="22%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="45%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%"></TD>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Related Person Transactions and Procedures </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">In accordance with SEC rules, ExxonMobil maintains Guidelines for Review of Related Person Transactions (&#147;Related Person Transaction Guidelines&#148;). These
guidelines are available on the Corporate Governance section of our website. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">In accordance with the Related Person Transaction Guidelines, all executive officers,
directors, and director nominees are required to identify, to the best of their knowledge after reasonable inquiry, business and financial affiliations involving themselves or their immediate family members that could reasonably be expected to give
rise to a reportable related person transaction. Covered persons must also advise the Secretary of the Corporation promptly of any change in the information provided, and will be asked periodically to review and reaffirm their information. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">For the above purposes, &#147;immediate family member&#148; includes a person&#146;s spouse, parents, siblings, children,
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">in-laws,</FONT> and step-relatives. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Based on this information, the Company&#146;s own records are reviewed and <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">follow-up</FONT> inquiries are made as may be necessary to identify potentially reportable transactions. A report summarizing such transactions and including a reasonable level of detail is then provided to the Board
Affairs Committee. The Committee oversees the Related Person Transaction Guidelines generally and reviews specific items to assess materiality. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">In assessing
materiality for this purpose, information will be considered material if, in light of all circumstances, there is a substantial likelihood that a reasonable investor would consider the information important in deciding whether to buy or sell
ExxonMobil stock or in deciding how to vote shares of ExxonMobil stock. A director will abstain from the decision on any transactions involving that director or his or her immediate family members. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Under SEC rules, certain transactions are deemed not to involve a material interest (including transactions in which the amount involved in any <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">12-month</FONT> period is less than $120,000 and transactions with entities where a related person&#146;s interest is limited to service as a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director). In addition,
based on a consideration of ExxonMobil&#146;s facts and circumstances, the Committee will presume that the following transactions do not involve a material interest for purposes of reporting under SEC rules: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Transactions in the ordinary course of business with an entity for which a related person serves as an executive officer,
<I>provided:</I> (1)&nbsp;the affected director or executive officer did not participate in the decision on the part of ExxonMobil to enter into such transactions; and (2)&nbsp;the amount involved in any related category of transactions in a <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">12-month</FONT> period is less than 1&nbsp;percent of the entity&#146;s gross revenues; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Grants or membership payments in the ordinary course of business to nonprofit organizations, <I>provided:</I> (1)&nbsp;the
affected director or executive officer did not participate in the decision on the part of ExxonMobil to make such payments; and (2)&nbsp;the amount of general purpose grants in a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">12-month</FONT> period is less than
1&nbsp;percent of the recipient&#146;s gross revenues; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Payments under ExxonMobil plans and arrangements that are available generally to U.S. salaried employees (including
contributions under the ExxonMobil Foundation&#146;s Educational and Cultural Matching Gift Programs and payments to providers under ExxonMobil health care plans); and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Employment by ExxonMobil of a family member of an executive officer, <I>provided</I> the executive officer does not
participate in decisions regarding the hiring, performance evaluation, or compensation of the family member. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Transactions or relationships not
covered by the above standards will be assessed by the Board Affairs Committee on the basis of the specific facts and circumstances. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Unless otherwise noted, the
following disclosures are made as of February&nbsp;26, 2019 which is the date of the most recent Board Affairs Committee review of potential related person transactions. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">ExxonMobil and its affiliates have more than 70,000 employees around the world and employees related by birth or marriage may be found at all levels of the
organization. ExxonMobil employees do not receive preferential treatment by reason of being related to an executive officer, and executive officers do not participate in hiring, performance </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">
evaluation, or compensation decisions for family members. ExxonMobil&#146;s employment guidelines state, &#147;Relatives of Company employees may be employed on a
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-preferential</FONT> basis. However, an employee should not be employed by or assigned to work under the direct supervision of a relative, or to report to a supervisor who in turn reports to a relative of the
employee.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Several current ExxonMobil executive officers and retirees who served as executive officers in 2018 have family members who are employed by the
Corporation or its affiliates and whose current annualized compensation (including benefits) exceeds the SEC disclosure threshold: N.A. Hansen (Vice President &#150; Investor Relations and Secretary) has a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">brother-in-law</FONT></FONT> employed by ExxonMobil Development Company; L.M. Mallon (President &#150; ExxonMobil Development Company) has a son employed by ExxonMobil Development Company; R.N. Schleckser (Vice President
and Treasurer) has a brother employed by ExxonMobil Research and Engineering Company; J.M. Spellings, Jr. (Vice President and General Tax Counsel) has a son employed by ExxonMobil Pipeline Company; T.J. Wojnar, Jr. (Vice President &#150; Corporate
Strategic Planning) has a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">son-in-law</FONT></FONT> employed by ExxonMobil Fuels&nbsp;&amp; Lubricants Company; and J.J. Woodbury (retired former Vice President &#150; Investor
Relations and Secretary) has a son employed by XTO Energy Inc. Consistent with ExxonMobil&#146;s Related Person Transaction Guidelines as described above, these relationships are not considered to be material within the meaning of the related person
transaction disclosure rules. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">S.N. Ortwein (retired former President, XTO Energy Inc) has a
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">brother-in-law</FONT></FONT> currently serving as Chief Executive Officer of Oracle Corporation. In the ordinary course of our business, ExxonMobil purchases a variety of computer
technology and services from Oracle. Ms.&nbsp;Ortwein had no involvement in decisions regarding ExxonMobil&#146;s business with Oracle and the annual volume of such business is well below the categorical threshold established in ExxonMobil&#146;s
Related Person Transaction Guidelines. R.M. Ebner (Vice President and General Counsel) has a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">brother-in-law</FONT></FONT> who is a partner of a law firm that performs limited work for
ExxonMobil. Mr.&nbsp;Ebner&#146;s <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">brother-in-law</FONT></FONT> does not work on ExxonMobil&#146;s account and Mr.&nbsp;Ebner is recused from any involvement in decisions to retain the
firm. Therefore, these relationships are not considered to be material within the meaning of the related person transaction disclosure rules. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board Affairs
Committee also reviewed ExxonMobil&#146;s ordinary course business with companies for which <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors or their immediate family members serve as executive officers. The Committee determined that,
in accordance with the categorical standards described above, none of those matters represent reportable related person transactions. See Director Independence on page 11. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Committee also determined that no related person transactions occurred during the year involving any of the investors who have reported ownership of more than
5&nbsp;percent of ExxonMobil&#146;s outstanding common stock. See Certain Beneficial Owners on page 26. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">ExxonMobil is not aware of any related person transactions
required to be reported under applicable SEC rules since the beginning of the last fiscal year where our policies and procedures did not require review, or where such policies and procedures were not followed. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Corporation&#146;s Related Person Transaction Guidelines are intended to assist the Corporation in complying with its disclosure obligations under SEC rules. These
procedures are in addition to, not in lieu of, the Corporation&#146;s Code of Ethics and Business Conduct. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Code of Ethics and Business Conduct </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board maintains policies and procedures (referred to in this proxy statement as the &#147;Code&#148;) that represent both the code of ethics for the principal
executive officer, principal financial officer, and principal accounting officer under SEC rules, and the code of business conduct and ethics for directors, officers, and employees under NYSE listing standards. The Code applies to all directors,
officers, and employees. The Code includes a Conflicts of Interest Policy under which directors, officers, and employees are expected to avoid any actual or apparent conflict between their own personal interests and the interests of the Corporation.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Code is posted on the ExxonMobil website at <I>exxonmobil.com/code</I>. The Code is also included as an exhibit to our <I>Annual Report on Form <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT></I>. Any amendment of the Code will be posted promptly on ExxonMobil&#146;s website. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
