<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Corporation maintains procedures for administering and reviewing potential issues under the Code, including
procedures that allow employees to make complaints without identifying themselves. The Corporation also conducts periodic mandatory business practice training sessions, and requires regular employees and
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors to complete annual compliance certifications. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board Affairs Committee will initially review any
suspected violation of the Code involving an executive officer or director and will report its findings to the Board. The Board does not envision that any waiver of the Code will be granted. Should such a waiver occur, it will be promptly disclosed
on ExxonMobil&#146;s website. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Board Meetings and Annual Meeting Attendance </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board met nine times in 2018. ExxonMobil&#146;s incumbent directors, on average, attended approximately 99&nbsp;percent of Board and committee meetings during 2018.
No director attended less than 75&nbsp;percent of such meetings. ExxonMobil&#146;s <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors held seven executive sessions in 2018. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">As specified in our Corporate Governance Guidelines, it is ExxonMobil&#146;s policy that directors should make every effort to attend the annual meeting of
shareholders. All incumbent directors attended last year&#146;s meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Board Committees </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board appoints committees to help carry out its duties. Board committees work on key issues in greater detail than would be possible at full Board meetings. Only <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors may serve on the Audit, Compensation, Board Affairs, and Public Issues and Contributions Committees. Each committee has a written charter. The charters are posted on the Corporate Governance
section of our website at <I>exxonmobil.com/governance</I>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The table below shows the current membership of each Board committee and the number of meetings each
committee held in 2018. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="96%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:9pt">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Review of any issue involving an executive officer or director under ExxonMobil&#146;s Code of Ethics and Business Conduct;
and </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Administration of ExxonMobil&#146;s Related Person Transaction Guidelines. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Committee also administers provisions of the Corporate Governance Guidelines that require a director to tender a resignation when there is a substantial change in
the director&#146;s circumstances. The Committee reviews the relevant facts to determine whether the director&#146;s continued service would be appropriate and makes a recommendation to the Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Another responsibility of the Committee is to review and make recommendations to the Board regarding the compensation of the
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors. The Committee uses an independent consultant, Pearl Meyer&nbsp;&amp; Partners, LLC (&#147;Pearl Meyer&#148;), to provide information on current developments and practices in director
compensation. Pearl Meyer is the same consultant retained by the Compensation Committee to advise on executive compensation, but performs no other work for ExxonMobil. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Guidelines for the Selection of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Employee</FONT> Directors describe the qualifications the Committee looks for in director
candidates. These Selection Guidelines, as well as the Committee&#146;s charter, are posted on the Corporate Governance section of our website. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Audit Committee
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Audit Committee oversees accounting and internal control matters. Its responsibilities include oversight of: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Management&#146;s conduct of the Corporation&#146;s financial reporting process; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

public; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">The performance of the Corporation&#146;s internal audit function; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">The independent auditors&#146; qualifications, performance, and independence; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">The annual independent audit of the Corporation&#146;s financial statements. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Committee has direct authority and responsibility to appoint (subject to shareholder ratification), compensate, retain, and oversee the independent auditors. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Committee also prepares the report that SEC rules require be included in the Corporation&#146;s annual proxy statement. This report is on pages 27 and 28. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Audit Committee has adopted specific policies and procedures for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approving</FONT> fees paid to the independent auditors. Under
the Audit Committee&#146;s approach, an annual program of work is approved each October for the following categories of services: Audit, Audit-Related, and Tax. Additional engagements may be brought forward from time to time for <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approval</FONT> by the Audit Committee. <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Pre-approvals</FONT> apply to engagements within a category of service, and cannot be transferred between categories. If fees might otherwise
exceed <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approved</FONT> amounts for any category of permissible services, the incremental amounts must be reviewed and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approved</FONT> prior to commitment. The complete text of
the Audit Committee&#146;s <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approval</FONT> policies and procedures, as well as the Committee&#146;s charter, is posted on the Corporate Governance section of ExxonMobil&#146;s website. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board has determined that all members of the Committee are financially literate within the meaning of the NYSE standards, and that Ms.&nbsp;Burns,
Mr.&nbsp;Oberhelman, and Mr.&nbsp;Weldon are &#147;audit committee financial experts&#148; as defined in the SEC rules. </P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Compensation Committee </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The
Compensation Committee is comprised exclusively of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee,</FONT> independent directors, and oversees compensation for ExxonMobil&#146;s senior executives (including salary, bonus, and performance share
awards), as well as succession planning for key executive positions. The Committee&#146;s charter is available on the Corporate Governance section of our website. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">During 2018, the Committee took the following actions: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Reviewed and approved the corporate goals and objectives relevant to the compensation of the CEO; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Reviewed the Corporation&#146;s business results and progress on strategic plans during the year with ExxonMobil&#146;s CEO
and other senior executives; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Carefully considered the results of the 2018 advisory vote on executive compensation; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Assessed each element of the Company&#146;s compensation program and practices, and confirmed that they do not create any
material adverse risks for the Company. The key design features of the compensation program that discourage executives from taking inappropriate risk are described in detail in this proxy statement (see pages 32, and 45 to 48);
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Discussed the Company&#146;s executive compensation program with its independent consultant; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Established the aggregate annual ceilings for the 2018 short-term and long-term incentive award programs taking into
account input received from the CEO and other senior executives; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Approved the salary program for 2019; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Reviewed the performance and contributions of, and granted incentive awards and salary for, the CEO. The CEO does not
participate in or provide input to decisions regarding his own compensation; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Reviewed the individual performance and contributions of, and granted individual incentive awards and set salaries for,
other senior executives based on recommendations to the Committee by the CEO; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Reviewed progress on executive development and succession planning for senior-level positions with input from the CEO.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Committee does not delegate its responsibilities with respect to ExxonMobil&#146;s executive officers and other senior executives (currently
21 positions). For other employees, the Committee delegates authority to determine individual salaries and incentive awards to a committee consisting of the Chairman and the Senior Vice Presidents of the Corporation. That committee&#146;s actions
are subject to a salary budget and aggregate annual ceilings on short-term and long-term incentive awards established by the Compensation Committee. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">For more
information on the compensation decisions made by the Committee for 2018, refer to the Compensation Discussion and Analysis (&#147;CD&amp;A&#148;) beginning on page 31. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Compensation Committee&#146;s report is available on page 30. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Compensation
Committee utilizes the expertise of an external independent consultant, Pearl Meyer. At the direction of the Committee, Pearl Meyer: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Compensation Committee is solely and directly responsible for the appointment, compensation, and oversight of the
consultant. The Committee considers factors that could affect Pearl Meyer&#146;s independence, including that the consultant provides no other services for ExxonMobil other than its engagement by the Committee and the Board Affairs Committee as
described above. Based on this review, the Committee has determined the consultant&#146;s work for the Committee to be free from conflicts of interest. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Finance
Committee </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Finance Committee reviews ExxonMobil&#146;s financial policies and strategies, including our capital structure, dividends, and share purchase
program. The Committee authorizes the issuance of corporate debt subject to limits set by the Board. The Committee&#146;s charter is available on the Corporate Governance section of our website. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Public Issues and Contributions Committee </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Public Issues and
Contributions Committee reviews the effectiveness of the Corporation&#146;s policies, programs, and practices with respect to safety, security, health, the environment, including climate-related matters, and social issues. The Committee hears
reports from operating units on safety and environmental activities, and also visits operating sites to observe and comment on current operating practices. In addition, the Committee reviews the level of ExxonMobil&#146;s support for education and
other public service programs, including the Company&#146;s contributions to the ExxonMobil Foundation. The Foundation works to improve the quality of education in the United States at all levels, with special emphasis on math and science. The
Foundation also supports the Company&#146;s other cultural and public service giving. The Committee&#146;s charter is available on the Corporate Governance section of our website. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Executive Committee </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Executive Committee has broad power to act on behalf
of the Board. In practice, the Committee meets only when it is impractical to call a meeting of the full Board. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="99%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8"> <P STYLE="font-size:3pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Shareholder Engagement</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">We believe ongoing engagement with our shareholders is vitally important. ExxonMobil understands the importance of keeping shareholders informed
about our business, understanding our shareholders&#146; perspectives, and addressing areas of interest. In 2018, the Company held shareholder engagements on environmental, social, and governance matters with institutional investors, pension funds,
and labor, religious, and nongovernmental organizations representing more than 1.3&nbsp;billion shares, or approximately 30&nbsp;percent of total shares outstanding and 55&nbsp;percent of institutional shareholdings. The number of engagements with
shareholders on environmental, social, and governance issues has more than doubled since 2014. Additionally, during 2018 we engaged with shareholders representing nearly 1&nbsp;billion shares on a range of other issues of importance to
ExxonMobil&#146;s business. Our engagement efforts include members of senior management, subject matter experts, and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Company communicates with shareholders through a variety of means,
including publications we issue throughout the year; our website (including the <I>Perspectives</I> blog); the annual shareholders meeting; webcasts, including our annual executive compensation and governance webcast during which any shareholder can
submit comments or questions; and through direct interface. We welcome and value input from all shareholders, and such input is taken seriously by the Company.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board Affairs Committee has approved and implemented procedures for shareholders and other interested persons to send written or electronic
communications to individual directors, including the Presiding Director, Board committees, or the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors as a group.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.50em; text-indent:-2.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8194;&#8201;<B>Written Communications: </B>Written
correspondence should be addressed to the director or directors in care of the Secretary at the address given under Contact Information on page 7.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.50em; text-indent:-2.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8194;&#8201;<B>Electronic Communications: </B>You may send <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">e-mail</FONT> to individual <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors, Board committees, or the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors as a group by using the form provided for
that purpose on our website at <I>exxonmobil.com/directors</I>.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:arial"><B><A NAME="toc686227_5"></A>Item&nbsp;1&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;Election of Directors </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board of Directors has nominated the director candidates named on the following pages. Personal information about each of our nominees, including public company
directorships during the past five years, is provided. Also included are the particular qualifications and competencies of each director nominee that led the Board to conclude that such person should serve as a director of the Company. <B>All of our
nominees currently serve as ExxonMobil directors.</B> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">All director nominees have stated they are willing to serve if elected. If a nominee becomes unavailable
before the election, your proxy authorizes the people named as proxies to vote for a replacement nominee if the Board names one. Alternatively, the Board may reduce its size to equal the number of remaining nominees. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B>The Board recommends you vote FOR each of the following candidates: </B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B>Susan K. Avery</B></FONT></P>

</P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Principal occupation:</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">President Emerita,</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Woods&nbsp;Hole&nbsp;Oceanographic</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Institution</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Age 69</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Director since 2017</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Independent director</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Committees:</B></P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Background:</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201;<B>Achieved prominence in her field </B>at the Woods
Hole Oceanographic Institution, a global research organization, as President and Director from 2008 to 2015. In the course of her lengthy and varied experience with matters of climate science, Dr.&nbsp;Avery has been involved with areas of policy,
carbon pricing, renewable energy, and adaptation.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201;<B>Academic leadership</B> at the University of Colorado Boulder as interim dean of the graduate school and vice chancellor for research, interim provost, and executive vice
chancellor for academic affairs from 2004 to 2008</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201;<B>Government / scientific research</B> experience as past member of the United Nations Scientific Advisory Board and the National Research Council Global Change Research Program
Advisory Committee</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201;<B>Scientific and research</B> advisory committee memberships held or recently held at NASA, NOAA, National Science Foundation, Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory, National
Park System, Independent Advisory Committee on Applied Climate Risk, Center for Southern Hemisphere Ocean Research, Qingdao National Laboratory for Marine Science and Technology, and Japan Agency for Marine-Earth Science and Technology</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201;<B>Scientific and environmental affiliations:</B>
University Corporation for Atmospheric Research (Chair of Board), Consortium for Ocean Leadership (senior fellow), American Geophysical Union, American Meteorological Society (fellow), American Association for the Advancement of Science (fellow),
and Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (fellow)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Current public company
directorships:</B> None</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Previous public company directorships in last five years:</B>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Committees:</B></P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

experience</B> at MetLife, Inc. as Chairman since 2012; as President and Chief Executive Office since 2011; and as Executive Vice President and Chief Investment Officer from 2005 to 2011. He also served as Executive Director of the Pension Benefit
Guaranty Corporation from 2001 to 2004.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201;<B>Academic leadership</B> at Wake Forest University
as Dean of Business from 2008 to 2014; and as Professor of Leadership and Strategy</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

Foundation (Board of Trustees), Newman&#146;s Own Foundation (Advisory Board), and Center for Creative Leadership (Board of Governors)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201;<B>Scientific, research, and academic affiliations:

(June 2010 to Present)</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Previous public company directorships in last five years:</B>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Chief Executive Officer,</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Exxon Mobil Corporation</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Committees:</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Finance, Executive</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Background:</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201;<B>Global business leadership</B> at Exxon Mobil
Corporation as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer since 2017; as President in 2016; and as Senior Vice President in 2014 and 2015. He also served as Vice President, and President, ExxonMobil Refining&nbsp;&amp; Supply Company from 2012 to
2014.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201;<B>Operational and commodity business </B>experience
with positions of increasing responsibility in domestic and international business operations at ExxonMobil Refining&nbsp;&amp; Supply Company, ExxonMobil Chemical Company, and Exxon Company International</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201;<B>Business affiliations:</B> Business Roundtable,
American Petroleum Institute (Chair), Business Council, Center for Strategic and International Studies (Trustee), Oil and Gas Climate Initiative, and National Petroleum Council</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.70em; text-indent:-1.70em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT>&#8195;&#8201;&#8201;<B>Scientific and environmental experience:
</B>ExxonMobil Chemical Company and ExxonMobil Refining&nbsp;&amp; Supply Company</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Current
public company directorships:</B> None</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Previous public company directorships in last five
years:</B><I> </I>Imperial Oil Ltd. (April&nbsp;2013 to July 2014)</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B><A NAME="toc686227_6"></A>Director Compensation </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Director compensation elements are designed to: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Ensure alignment with long-term shareholder interests; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Ensure the Company can attract and retain outstanding director candidates who meet the selection criteria outlined in the
Guidelines for Selection of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-Employee</FONT> Directors, which can be found on the Corporate Governance section of our website; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Recognize the substantial time commitment necessary to oversee the affairs of the Corporation; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">Support the independence of thought and action expected of directors. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> director compensation levels are reviewed by the Board Affairs Committee each year, and resulting recommendations
are presented to the full Board for approval. The Committee uses an independent consultant, Pearl Meyer, to provide information on current developments and practices in director compensation. Pearl Meyer is the same consultant retained by the
Compensation Committee to advise on executive compensation, but performs no other work for ExxonMobil. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">ExxonMobil employees receive no additional pay for serving
as directors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> directors receive compensation consisting of cash and equity in the form of restricted stock. <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> directors are also reimbursed for reasonable expenses incurred to attend Board meetings or other functions relating to their responsibilities as a director of Exxon Mobil Corporation. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The annual cash retainer for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors in 2018 was $110,000 per year. Chairs of the Audit and Compensation
Committees and the Presiding Director receive an additional $10,000 per year. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">A significant portion of director compensation is granted in the form of restricted
stock to align director interests with the interests of our long-term shareholders. The annual restricted stock award grant for incumbent <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors is 2,500 shares. A new <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director receives a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-time</FONT> grant of 8,000 shares of restricted stock upon first being elected to the Board. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>

<TD></TD>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">While on the Board, the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director receives the same cash dividends
on restricted shares as a holder of regular common stock, but the shares remain unvested and, thus, cannot be sold or pledged. The restricted shares are subject to forfeiture if the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director
leaves the Board early, i.e., before the retirement age of 72, as specified for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Current and former <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors of Exxon Mobil Corporation are eligible to participate in the ExxonMobil Foundation&#146;s Educational and Cultural Matching Gift Programs under the same terms as the Corporation&#146;s U.S.
employees. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Director Compensation for 2018 </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="96%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:9pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="86%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>

benefits as a result of leaving the Board or death except as described above. The <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors are not entitled to any payments or benefits resulting from a change in control of the Corporation. </P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B><A NAME="toc686227_8"></A>Director and Executive Officer Stock Ownership </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">These tables show the number of ExxonMobil common shares each executive named in the Summary Compensation Table on page 49 and each
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director or director nominee owned on February&nbsp;28, 2019. In these tables, ownership means the right to direct the voting or the sale of shares, even if those rights are shared with someone
else. None of these individuals owns more than 0.02&nbsp;percent of the outstanding shares. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">On February&nbsp;28, 2019, ExxonMobil&#146;s incumbent directors and executive officers (27 people) together owned
2,204,887 shares of ExxonMobil stock and zero shares covered by exercisable options, representing about 0.05&nbsp;percent of the outstanding shares. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Section&nbsp;16(a) Beneficial Ownership Reporting Compliance </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Section&nbsp;16(a) of the Securities and Exchange Act of 1934 requires our executive officers and directors to file reports of their ownership and changes in ownership
of ExxonMobil stock on Forms 3, 4, and 5 with the SEC. We are not aware of any unfiled or late reports for 2018. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B><A NAME="toc686227_9"></A>Audit Committee Report </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The primary function of our Audit Committee is oversight of the Corporation&#146;s financial reporting process, public financial reports, internal accounting and
financial controls, and the independent audit of the annual consolidated financial statements. Our Committee acts under a charter, which can be found on the ExxonMobil website at <I>exxonmobil.com/auditcommitteecharter.</I> We review the adequacy of
the charter at least annually. All of our members are independent directors. We held 11 meetings in 2018 at which, as discussed in more detail below, we had extensive reports and discussions with the independent auditors, internal auditors, and
members of management. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">In performing our oversight function, we reviewed and discussed the consolidated financial statements with management and
PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP (&#147;PwC&#148;), the independent auditors. Management and PwC indicated that the Corporation&#146;s consolidated financial statements were fairly stated in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles. We
discussed significant accounting policies applied by the Corporation in its financial statements, as well as alternative treatments. We discussed with PwC matters covered by Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (&#147;PCAOB&#148;) standards,
including PCAOB AS 1301 <I>Communication with Audit Committees</I>. In addition, we reviewed and discussed management&#146;s report on internal control over financial reporting and the related audits performed by PwC, which confirmed the
effectiveness of the Corporation&#146;s internal control over financial reporting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">We also discussed with PwC its independence from the Corporation and management,
including the communications PwC is required to provide us under applicable PCAOB rules. We considered the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-audit</FONT> services provided by PwC to the Corporation, and concluded that the auditors&#146;
independence has been maintained. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">We discussed with the Corporation&#146;s internal auditors and PwC the overall scope and plans for their respective audits. We
met with the internal auditors and PwC at each meeting, both with and without management present. Discussions included the results of their examinations, their evaluations of the Corporation&#146;s internal controls, and the overall quality of the
Corporation&#146;s financial reporting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">We discussed with the Corporation&#146;s management the comprehensive, long-standing risk management and compliance
processes of the Corporation, and reviewed several topics of interest. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Based on the reviews and discussions referred to above, in reliance on management and PwC,
and subject to the limitations of our role described below, we recommended to the Board, and the Board approved, the inclusion of the audited financial statements in the Corporation&#146;s <I>Annual Report on Form
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT></I> for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2018, for filing with the SEC. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">In carrying out our responsibilities, we look
to management and the independent auditors. Management is responsible for the preparation and fair presentation of the Corporation&#146;s financial statements and for maintaining effective internal control. Management is also responsible for
assessing and maintaining the effectiveness of internal control over the financial reporting process in compliance with Sarbanes-Oxley Section&nbsp;404 requirements. The independent auditors are responsible for auditing the Corporation&#146;s annual
financial statements, and expressing an opinion as to whether the statements are fairly stated in conformity with generally accepted accounting principles. In addition, the independent auditors are responsible for auditing the Corporation&#146;s
internal control over financial reporting and for expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting. The </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">
independent auditors perform their responsibilities in accordance with the standards of the PCAOB. Our members are not professionally engaged in the practice of accounting or auditing, and are
not experts under the Securities Act of 1933 in either of those fields or in auditor independence. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">We have also appointed PwC to audit the Corporation&#146;s
financial statements for 2019, subject to shareholder ratification of that appointment. The Committee annually evaluates, along with the other members of the Board, management, the Controller, and the General Auditor, PwC&#146;s qualifications,
performance, and independence, including the performance of the lead audit partner, in deciding whether or not to retain PwC. That evaluation includes consideration of: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">PwC&#146;s quality control, including any material issues identified by that quality control or a governmental/professional
authority along with PwC&#146;s plan to deal with any such issues; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">All relationships between PwC and ExxonMobil covered by the PCAOB; </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">PwC&#146;s expertise in the global oil and gas industry; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">The quality of PwC&#146;s audit plans. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Committee believes that PwC&#146;s tenure as ExxonMobil&#146;s independent registered public accounting firm is a benefit to audit quality given PwC&#146;s
experience with ExxonMobil and knowledge of the business, as well as the effectiveness of their audit plans, which build on that established knowledge. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Based on
the Committee&#146;s annual evaluation of PwC&#146;s qualifications, performance, and independence, as well as frequent private meetings with the lead partner, we believe that the continued retention of PwC as ExxonMobil&#146;s independent
registered public accounting firm is in the best interest of the Corporation and its stockholders. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:arial"><B><A NAME="toc686227_10"></A>Item&nbsp;2&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;Ratification of Independent Auditors </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Audit Committee has appointed PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP (&#147;PwC&#148;) to audit ExxonMobil&#146;s financial statements for 2019. We are asking you to ratify that
appointment. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Total Fees </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The total fees for PwC professional services
rendered to ExxonMobil for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2018, were $41.2&nbsp;million, a decrease of $3.9&nbsp;million from 2017. The Audit Committee reviewed and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approved</FONT> all services in accordance
with the service <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approval</FONT> policies and procedures, which can be found on the ExxonMobil website at <I><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">exxonmobil.com/pre-approval.</FONT></I> The Audit Committee did not
use the &#147;de minimis&#148; exception to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-approval</FONT> that is available under SEC rules. The following table summarizes the fees, which are described in more detail below. </P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Audit Fees </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The aggregate fees for PwC
professional services rendered for the annual audits of ExxonMobil&#146;s financial statements for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2018, and for the reviews of the financial statements included in our quarterly reports on Form <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-Q</FONT> for that year were $31.4&nbsp;million (versus $32.2&nbsp;million for 2017), with the decrease primarily due to lower acquisition-related work and foreign exchange impacts. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Audit-Related Fees </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The
aggregate fees for PwC Audit-Related services rendered to ExxonMobil for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2018, were $8.8&nbsp;million (versus $11.4&nbsp;million for 2017), with the decrease primarily due to lower regulatory support work.
Audit-related services were mainly related to benefit plan audits and other attestation procedures. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>Tax Fees </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The aggregate fees for PwC Tax services rendered to ExxonMobil for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2018, were $1.0&nbsp;million (versus $1.5&nbsp;million for 2017),
with the decrease primarily due to lower acquisition-related work. These services were mainly related to assisting various ExxonMobil affiliates with the preparation of local tax filings and related services. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>All Other Fees </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The aggregate fees for PwC services rendered to ExxonMobil,
other than the services described above under &#147;Audit Fees,&#148; &#147;Audit-Related Fees,&#148; and &#147;Tax Fees,&#148; for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2018, were zero (also zero for 2017). </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">We believe PwC is well qualified to perform this work. A PwC representative will be at the annual meeting to answer appropriate questions and to make a statement if
desired. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B>The Audit Committee recommends you vote FOR this proposal. </B></FONT></P>

<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B><A NAME="toc686227_11"></A>Compensation Committee Report </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Compensation Committee of the Board of Directors has reviewed and discussed the Compensation Discussion and Analysis with management of the Corporation. Based on
that review and discussion, we recommended to the Board that the Compensation Discussion and Analysis be included in the Corporation&#146;s proxy statement for the 2019 annual meeting of shareholders, and also incorporated by reference in the
Corporation&#146;s <I>Annual Report on Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT></I> for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2018. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="48%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Samuel J. Palmisano, Chair</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">Angela F. Braly</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Kenneth C. Frazier</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">Steven A. Kandarian</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:arial"><B><A NAME="toc686227_12"></A>Item&nbsp;3&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;Advisory Vote to Approve Executive Compensation </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">At the meeting, shareholders will be asked to vote on a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-binding</FONT> resolution to approve the compensation of the Named Executive
Officers (NEOs), listed in the Summary Compensation Table. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">When casting your vote, we encourage you to consider the content of our Executive Compensation Overview
and detailed information included in the Compensation Discussion and Analysis beginning on page 31. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">The Board continues to support the overall design of the
compensation program, which is characterized by three key features: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt"><B>Ties executive compensation to the returns of long-term shareholders</B>&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;The majority of compensation
is delivered in the form of performance shares, linking the ultimate value of pay to the performance of ExxonMobil stock. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt"><B>Recognizes the long-term nature of ExxonMobil&#146;s business model</B><B></B>&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;Performance shares are
subject to the longest restriction periods in the industry, including through the commodity price cycle. A significant portion of executive pay vests only after retirement. Therefore, executives are encouraged to take a long-term view in their
business decision making. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt"><B>Links executives&#146; compensation to Company performance</B><B></B>&nbsp;&#150;&nbsp;The number of shares at grant is
determined by relative Company performance versus industry peers, progress toward strategic objectives including strengthening the Company&#146;s growth strategy, and market orientation of total compensation. We set the highest performance
standards, requiring industry-leading results over the investment lead times of the business in <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-established</FONT> metrics. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">For 2018, Company performance remains industry leading in all but one of these performance metrics, Total Shareholder Return (TSR). Compensation levels for the CEO and
NEOs reflect these results. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">We continue to listen and respond to the feedback we receive from shareholders during our shareholder engagement process. As in
previous years, we enhanced disclosures in response to shareholder feedback. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#2b4c9b"><B>The Board recommends an advisory vote FOR the
following resolution: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">RESOLVED: That shareholders approve the compensation of the Named Executive Officers as disclosed pursuant to Item 402 of SEC
Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K,</FONT> including the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, compensation tables, and narrative discussion on pages 31 to 57 of this proxy statement. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="80%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial narrow; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.10em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">30&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><A HREF="#tx686227_1">Letter to Shareholders</A></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-bottom:1pt; margin-top:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-bottom:1pt; margin-top:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial" ALIGN="right">32</P></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-bottom:1pt; margin-top:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"><A HREF="#tx686227_2">Strong Governance Practices</A></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="right">32</TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD></TR>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center"><A NAME="tx686227_1"></A>


<IMG SRC="g686227g72v50.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P ALIGN="center" STYLE="font-family:arial; font-size:0.5pt"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF">LETTER TO SHAREHOLDERS Fellow Shareholders, Before you cast your vote on Management Resolution Item 3 - Advisory Vote to Approve
Executive Compensation, the members of the Board's independent Compensation Committee encourage you to review the content of this Executive Compensation Overview, as well as the additional detail provided in the Compensation Discussion and Analysis,
compensation tables, and narrative in ExxonMobil's 2019 Proxy Statement. The Compensation Committee reviews the effectiveness and competitiveness of the executive compensation program on an annual basis. ExxonMobil's business involves large
investments over long periods of time that require executives to maintain a long-term view when making business decisions. The Company's executive compensation program is designed to reflect this. The Compensation Committee continues to support the
design of the executive compensation program. It allows the Committee to leverage the experience and judgment of its members, across a mix of critical performance factors, to grant pay to executives that is both performance-based and aligned with
the returns of our long-term shareholders. We encourage you to vote "FOR" Item 3. Samuel J. Palmisano Chair, ExxonMobil Compensation Committee </FONT></P>
<div style ="background-color:#e2e8e8; max-width:100%">

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial"><B><A NAME="tx686227_3"></A>EXECUTIVE SUMMARY</B> &#150; WHY VOTE &#147;FOR&#148; <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">SAY-ON-PAY?</FONT></FONT> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#515959"><B>EXECUTIVE PAY IS ALIGNED WITH
<FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#ff0c00">COMPANY PERFORMANCE</FONT> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:20pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10.5pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10.5pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.98em; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial">Significant progress toward strategic goals led to an
increase in number of performance shares granted to CEO, balanced against relative TSR performance that did not lead the average of industry peers</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.95em; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:arial">Maintained industry-leading performance across all other pre-established metrics</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.95em; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:arial">2018 bonus program increased as a result of higher 2018 earnings</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.95em; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:arial">Pay for CEO position is at 44th percentile of CEO compensation benchmarks<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#515959"><B>PROGRAM TIES EXECUTIVE PAY TO <FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#ff0c00">SHAREHOLDER RETURNS</FONT>
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:20pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10.5pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10.5pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.95em; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:arial">Over 60 percent of CEO pay is in performance shares,
with longest restriction periods in any industry</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.95em; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:arial">Long-term incentive
program results in executives holding much higher percentage of performance shares through full business and commodity price cycles</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.95em; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:arial">Compensation program design makes long-term investors of our executives</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.95em; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:arial">Executives incentivized to maximize long-term shareholder returns and value while effectively managing risks, including environmental
risks</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14.5pt; font-family:arial"><FONT COLOR="#515959"><B>ENHANCED DISCLOSURE IN RESPONSE TO <FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" COLOR="#ff0c00">SHAREHOLDER
FEEDBACK</FONT> </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:20pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:arial; font-size:10.5pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="100%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:arial; font-size:10.5pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.95em; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:arial">Provided further clarification on the process and
considerations used by the Compensation Committee to determine CEO pay</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.95em; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:arial">Illustrated how performance share program aligns with business model</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.95em; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:arial">Strengthened disclosure of Company performance metrics that determine share grants</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:0.95em; font-size:10.5pt; font-family:arial">Clarified operation of delayed portion of annual bonus</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:48pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:7.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial"><B><A NAME="tx686227_4"></A>BUSINESS</B> OVERVIEW </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">To fully understand the rationale for the design of ExxonMobil&#146;s executive compensation program, it is important to understand the industry in which we operate. The
decisions and risks that our executives face play out over time horizons that are often decades in length. Therefore, the intent of the compensation program is to incentivize long-term decision making and align executives&#146; pay with the results
of their decisions and the returns of our long-term shareholders. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:arial">The Company&#146;s strategies provide the framework for the organization to deliver on its
commitments, create shareholder value throughout the commodity price cycle, and address the dual challenge of meeting the growing demand for energy while reducing environmental impacts. For more information, see the <I>Summary Annual Report</I>.<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</SUP> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:48pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial"><B><A NAME="tx686227_5"></A>COMPENSATION PROGRAM</B> DESIGN </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:48pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial"><B><A NAME="tx686227_6"></A>PERFORMANCE</B> <B>SHARE</B> PROGRAM </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:arial"><B>DESIGN PRINCIPLES </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
